        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@frank frank_]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/u/frank">@frank</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>i found this code in an old rsc client ive got</p>
<p><code>
        // picFile - the file where the image will be saved
        File picFile = new File("../Screenshots/", "Pic"+ picNumber +".png");
        // construct a new BufferedImage (you will have to change the size for the rs2 applet
        BufferedImage picBufferedImage = new BufferedImage(512, 347, java.awt.image.BufferedImage.TYPE_INT_RGB);
        // create the graphics
        Graphics picGraphics = picBufferedImage.createGraphics();
        /* draw the clients off-screen image (search through the classes for a field of type Image and swap it with dnb.bmb)
           'this' is assuming you place the code in a subclass of Applet, ie. client */
        picGraphics.drawImage(dnb.bmb, 0, 0, this);
        // clean up
        picGraphics.dispose();
        // write to file
        ImageIO.write(picBufferedImage, "png", picFile);</code><br>
i doubt my documenting will help, but i tried <img src="https://forum.moparisthebest.com/images/emoji/twitter/wink.png?v=6" title=":wink:" class="emoji" alt=":wink:"></p>
<p>you will also need these imports</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">java.awt.image.BufferedImage
java.io.File
java.awt.Graphics
javax.imageio.ImageIO</code></pre>
